Tunde Oyekola A Kwara State high court sitting in Ilorin has sentenced two internet fraudsters, Oyedele Olamide and Abdulrahman Mohammed, to two years’ imprisonment. The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission, Ilorin zonal office, had charged the two persons separately before the court for impersonation and fraud. The EFCC alleged that Abdulrahman (alias Fox Tim) on September 28, 2019 pretended to be Fox Tim and received a $50 iTunes gift card through his email account from one Brian Kelly, an American citizen. The offence according to the prosecution was contrary to Section 321 of the Penal Code and punishable under Section 324 of the same Panal Code. It also alleged that Oyedele Olamide between the month of April and December 2019, in Ilorin represented himself as a white female named Kaithlyn William to one Damir Hodzic via his email address in other to induce him (Hodzic) to send him money. “The offence was contrary to Section 95 of the Penal Code and punishable under Section 324 of the same Law,” the EFCC stated. Both Abdulrahman and Oyedele pleaded guilty to the separate charges brought against them. Delivering the judgment, Justice Sikiru Oyinloye, said the prosecution had proved its case beyond reasonable doubts. He then convicted “the two accused persons to the term of imprisonment of two years each.” Copyright PUNCH.
